==English==
===Etymology===
From Anglo-French Bretun, from [[w:Latin|Latin]][[Category:Latin derivations]] Brittonem (meaning "a member of the tribe of the Britons") from Britt-os, the Celtic name of the Celtic inhabitants of Britain and southern Scotland before the 5c, [[w:Old English language|Anglo-Saxon]][[Category:Anglo-Saxon derivations]] bryten.
